The utility announced it has lost six additional generating units, which has placed additional strain on the system. JOHANNESBURG - Power utility Eskom has announced that stage 4 load shedding will be implemented between 1pm and 10pm today. The utility says it has lost six additional generating units since this morning, which has placed additional strain on the system.  The utility explains that stage 1 requires 1,000 MW, stage 2 requires 2,000 MW, stage 3 requires 3,000 MW and stage 4 calls for 4,000 MW to be rotationally load shed nationally at a given period. "Load shedding is conducted rotationally as a measure of last resort to protect the power system." Check your area's load shedding schedule here.